{{Unreferenced|date= December 2014}} {{Campaignbox Campaigns of Muhammad}} '''Abu Hudhayfa ibn Utbah''' (Arabic: أبو حذيفة بن عتبة; died 633), full name '''Abu Hudhayfa ibn Utbah ibn Rabi'ah''' was an early companion of the Islamic prophet [[Muhammad]]. He was the son of [[Utbah ibn Rabi'ah]], one of the Leaders of Banu Abd Shams. He was the brother of [[Walid ibn Utbah]] and [[Hind bint Utbah]], the wife of [[Abu Sufyan]].
