=== North America === ;Canada {{main|List of reportedly haunted locations in Canada}} * [[Emily Carr]] allegedly haunts James Bay Inn in Victoria, British Columbia. * [[Francis Nicholson Darke]] allegedly haunts Darke Hall in Regina, Saskatchewan. * The [[Dungarvon Whooper]] is a ghost believed to haunt Blackville, New Brunswick. * [[Charles Melville Hays]] allegedly haunts Château Laurier in Ottawa, Ontario. * The [[Headless Nun]] is a purported ghost believed to haunt French Fort Cove in Nordin, New Brunswick. * Minnie Hopkins, wife of [[Edward Nicholas Hopkins]], allegedly haunts Hopkins Dining Parlour in Moose Jaw, Saskatchewan. * [[Alexander Keith (Canadian politician)|Alexander Keith]] allegedly haunts his [[Alexander Keith's Brewery|brewery]] in Halifax, Nova Scotia. * [[Nils von Schoultz]] allegedly haunts Fort Henry in Kingston, Ontario. * [[Aeneas Shaw]]'s daughter, Sophia allegedly haunts Queenston, Ontario. * [[Lady in Red (ghost)|Lady in Red]] * [[White Lady (ghost)|White Lady]]
